There are no terms, no conditions for using code of DanhUtils.


	-------------------------- DESCRIPTION -------------------------

Version: 0.0.8

Lines of code: 488

Authors:
	Daniel Housar (daniel.h.080490.cs@gmail.com)
	Matthew Fernandez (matthew.fernandez@gmail.com)

Danhutils is set of miscelaneous utilities, mostly using Libdanh library.
Libdanh is general purpose C library with various functions. Libdanh is shipped with Danhutils.


	---------------------------- UTILS -----------------------------

libdanh:
	- version: 0.8 rev. 11
	C library with some functions, for example sqrt_fd_dh() as implemetation of sqrt()
	from standard library math

quadequi:
	- version: 0.9
	Frontend of quadequi_fd_dh() from libdanh library.
	Computes roots of equation "ax^2 + bx + c = 0" if a b c values given as command line arguments and prints x1 and x2 values.

datatypes:
	- version: 0.5
	Prints sizeof() of standard types and sometimes max value and C preprocessor defines

portping:
	- version 0.1
	- License: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0
	- Author: Matthew Fernandez (matthew.fernandez@gmail.com)

	TCP/UDP connectivity diagnostic tool.
	If host and port given as command-line args, it pings once the port on given host if accessible and opened.
	!Now buildable under GNU/Linux, Mostly cann't be compilled under most MinGW setups!

	TODO: fix building under MinGW setups


	-------------------- BUILD & INSTALL ---------------------------

GNU Linux:
	$ cd /home/user/src/danhutils
	$ make
	$ make install

	- installs utils to '/usr/bin' by default
	- installs libdanh.so to '/usr/lib' by default
	- installs headers to '/usr/include/libdanh' by default

Windows (MinGW32):
	- Before running mingw32-make you have to install GCC and make from MinGW package from http://www.mingw.org/
	- Don't forget add "C:\mingw\bin" to PATH system variable

	> cd C:\Users\user\src\danhutils
	> mingw32-make -f Makefile-mingw32
	> mingw32-make -f Makefile-mingw32 install

	- installs utils and libdanh.dll to 'C:\bin' by default
	- installs headers to 'C:\include\libdanh' by default

